Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Transfer half the beans to a #bowl{} and mash with a #fork{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams} and @mayonnaise{32%grams}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to combine and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%grams} and @sliced mushrooms{80%grams} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{1%sachet} and cook for a further ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the mashed and whole beans, @smoky base paste{1%sachet}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{100%milliliters} for the sauce. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from the heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When everything's ready, pop the @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person) into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Reheat the refried beans if needed.

Toss the @wild rocket{20%grams} through the slaw.

> TIP: Don't do this too early or the leaves will go soggy!

When everything's ready, lay the tortillas onto your #serving plates{}.

Top with the rocket slaw, chorizo and refried beans. Sprinkle over the cheese to finish.

Serve the wedges alongside.

Enjoy!